nodes.bodyText: There should be just one .gitignore file at the root of the repository. Can you update this .gitignore instead?
Since this is in sdk/core/, should the artifactId be named azure-core-perftest? Also, is it perfstress or perftest?
Why not use Math.pow() method instead of implementing own power method?
Are all the perf tests pinned to JDK 8 or can we have two profiles to run these tests for both JDK 8 and 11?
I chose the name perfstress because this is a framework for both perf and stress testing.  But feel free to rename if you want.
I was afraid of the conversion between double and int.  But if you know this is safe you can replace with Math.pow().
Ideally we should be able to run perf tests on all supported JDK versions.  My Java expertise is limited so if anything looks wrong in the pom.xml files it probably is wrong :).
If you are planning on removing it later, then it's fine but don't want to have multiple places having this .gitignore configuration.
Since it's not going to be released, I am not too worried about the name as it can be changed later too.
Math.pow() works for this usecase, we can replace it
@mikeharder the pom.xml file looks correct, just wanted to ensure that we can support both JDK 8 and 11. We can add two profiles like @g2vinay said to support both.
